1) Project Report on Customer Relationship Management (CRM) Using Agile
1. Introduction

Customer Relationship Management (CRM) is a system used to manage customer details, interactions, leads, and sales process. The main purpose of CRM is to improve customer satisfaction and help companies maintain a good relationship with customers. This project focuses on building a simple CRM system using Agile methodology.

2. Objective

To store customer information in one place

To manage leads and follow-ups

To track customer communication history

To improve customer service and sales performance

3. Scope of the Project

This CRM system includes:

Customer registration and profile management

Lead tracking

Follow-up reminders

Customer support tickets

Basic reports (like number of customers, leads status)

4. Agile Methodology Used

Agile is a flexible development method where work is divided into small parts called sprints. Instead of completing the whole project at once, we build it step by step and take feedback after each sprint.

Sprint Plan

Sprint 1: Login + Customer module
Sprint 2: Lead module + follow-up system
Sprint 3: Ticket system + reports
Sprint 4: Testing + final improvements

5. Tools & Technologies

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

Backend: Java / PHP / Node (as per implementation)

Database: MySQL

Tools: VS Code / Eclipse, GitHub

6. System Requirements
Hardware:

Minimum 4GB RAM

Intel i3 or above

10GB free storage

Software:

Windows 10/11

MySQL Server

Browser (Chrome)

7. Conclusion

CRM system helps in maintaining customer relationships and improving service. Using Agile made the development easy because we could test and improve after every sprint.
